<b>Insalata Caprese</b> (salad in the style of <island wordnetid="109316454" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../223/295223.xml">
Capri</link></island>
) is a simple salad from the Italian region of <region wordnetid="108630039" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../943/44943.xml">
Campania</link></region>
, made of sliced fresh <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../632/20632.xml">
mozzarella</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../827/3736827.xml">
plum tomato</link>es and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../865/346865.xml">
basil</link>. It is seasoned with <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../200/1605200.xml">
salt</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../116/150116.xml">
black pepper</link>, and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../478/22478.xml">
olive oil</link>.  <ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%221%22])">1</ref></p>
<p>

Ideally, the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../632/20632.xml">
mozzarella</link> is <it><link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../035/1852035.xml">
di bufala campana</link></it>, the olive oil is <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../478/22478.xml#xpointer(//*[./st=%22Grades+on+retail+labels%22])">
extra virgin</link> from the peninsula of <site wordnetid="108651247" confidence="0.8">
<region wordnetid="108630985" confidence="0.8">
<administrative_district wordnetid="108491826" confidence="0.8">
<location wordnetid="100027167" confidence="0.8">
<tract wordnetid="108673395" confidence="0.8">
<municipality wordnetid="108626283" confidence="0.8">
<geographical_area wordnetid="108574314" confidence="0.8">
<district wordnetid="108552138" confidence="0.8">
<urban_area wordnetid="108675967" confidence="0.8">
<city wordnetid="108524735" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../580/172580.xml">
Sorrento</link></city>
</urban_area>
</district>
</geographical_area>
</municipality>
</tract>
</location>
</administrative_district>
</region>
</site>
 and the tomatoes and basil are grown in the full sun of the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../351/897351.xml">
mezzogiorno</link>.</p>
<p>

The dish reproduces the colours of the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../853/297853.xml">
flag of Italy</link>.</p>

