According to the 2006 edition of <it><book wordnetid="106410904" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../951/1045951.xml">
The Joy of Cooking</link></book>
 (75th Anniversary Edition)</it> page no. 169, Insalata Caprese (or Tomato and Mozzarella Salad) is prepared by arranging alternating ½ in. thick slices of tomatoes and ¼ in. slices of mozzarella on a platter, sprinkling with fresh basil leaves, drizzling with olive oil, and then seasoning with salt.</entry>
